      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Opinions on this debate remain deeply divided, as some experts believe current renewable technology paired with rapid grid scaling can achieve net-zero targets without immediate nuclear reliance. Others argue that the sheer pace required to meet 2050 goals makes the baseload stability and current scalability of nuclear energy indispensable for a viable transition. Scientific modeling suggests there is no single \"perfect\" solution, but rather that avoiding climate catastrophe likely requires a diversified portfolio where the specific role of nuclear depends heavily on local infrastructure and resource availability.",
